'''John Daniel Caine''' (born 10 August 1968) is an American retired lieutenant general (3-star) and [[Venture capital|venture capitalist]] who served as the [[Associate Director for Military Affairs of the Central Intelligence Agency|associate director for military affairs]] of the [[Central Intelligence Agency]] from 2021 to 2024. In February 2025, he was named as President [[Donald Trump]]'s nominee for [[chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff]], following the dismissal of [[Charles Q. Brown Jr.|General Charles Q. Brown Jr.]]

Caine graduated from the [[Virginia Military Institute]] in 1990. He was commissioned shortly thereafter, serving in various roles within the [[United States Air Force]]. He served as a deputy commanding general for [[Operation Inherent Resolve]] from 2018 to 2019 and the director of special-access programs in the [[Office of the Under Secretary of Defense for Acquisition and Sustainment]] from 2019 to 2021.

In February 2025, Trump dismissed Brown as the chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, naming Caine as his nominee to replace him. If confirmed, Caine would be the first chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff to have never served at the rank of [[general (United States)|general]] or [[admiral (United States)|admiral]] before assuming the position and the second to have been retired at the time of their confirmation after [[Maxwell D. Taylor]].

==Early life and education (1968–1990)==
Caine was born on 10 August 1968,{{Sfn|Ml John Daniel Caine in the U.S., Public Records Index, 1950-1993, Volume 1}} at St. Joseph's Hospital in [[Elmira, New York]].{{Sfn|"Births in Area". Star-Gazette (1968)}} He is the first child of Steven Allen Caine and Catherine Johnston Caine.{{Sfn|"Births in Area". Star-Gazette (1970)}}{{Efn|Steven and Catherine had one child after Caine: Jennifer{{Sfn|"Martin-Caine". Daily News-Record (1993)}} (born 1970).{{Sfn|"Births in Area". Star-Gazette (1970)}}}} Steven was a fighter pilot.{{Sfn|Copp|2025}} He graduated from Hahn American High School in [[Hahn, Rhineland-Palatinate]], [[Germany]].{{Sfn|"Martin-Caine". Daily News-Record (1992)}} In 1990, Caine graduated from the [[Virginia Military Institute]] with a degree in economics.{{Sfn|Cooper|Schmitt|2025}} He later graduated from [[American Military University]] with a master's degree in air warfare.{{Sfn|Cooper|Schmitt|2025}}

==Career==
===Military service (1990–2024)===
[[File:BG Caine Visits Mosul 4.jpg|thumb|Caine in [[Mosul]], [[Iraq]], in June 2018]]
