'''Dmitry Yuryevich Bivol''' ({{langx|ru|Дмитрий Юрьевич Бивол}}; born 18 December 1990) is a Russian [[professional boxer]]. He has held the [[undisputed championship (boxing)|undisputed]]{{efn|Four-belt era: [[World Boxing Association]] (WBA) ([[WBA (Super)|Super version]]), [[World Boxing Council]] (WBC), [[International Boxing Federation]] (IBF), and [[World Boxing Organization]] (WBO) titles.}}, [[International Boxing Organization]] (IBO), and the ''[[The Ring (magazine)|Ring]]'' magazine world [[light-heavyweight]] championship since February 2025. Previously, he held the WBA (Super) title from from 2019 to 2024. He also held the IBO title during his first reign as champion.

As an [[amateur boxing|amateur]], he won a gold medal at the [[2013 World Combat Games]] in the 81&nbsp;kg weight category.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.getsurrey.co.uk/sport/other-sport/boxer-ball-battles-world-silver-6240765|title=Boxer Ball battles to world silver medal in Russia - October 25 2013|date=25 October 2013}}</ref> He was listed by multiple sources as the fighter of the year for 2022,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-12-16 |title=Boxing's best of 2022: The knockouts, fights and fighters of the year |url=https://www.espn.com/boxing/story/_/id/35204488/boxing-best-2022-knockouts-fights-fighters-year |access-date=2023-11-26 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |last=Mannix |first=Chris |date=2022-12-27 |title=Dmitry Bivol Is Sports Illustrated's 2022 Fighter of the Year |url=https://www.si.com/boxing/2022/12/27/dmitrii-bivol-fighter-of-the-year-2022 |access-date=2023-11-26 |magazine=Sports Illustrated |language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Stillerman |first=James |date=2023-01-13 |title=2022 Fighter-of-the-Year: Dmitry Bivol - Boxing News |url=https://www.boxing247.com/boxing-news/2022-fighter-of-the-year-dmitry-bivol/256732 |access-date=2023-11-26 |website=www.boxing247.com |language=en-US}}</ref> including being selected as [[The Ring magazine Fighter of the Year|''The Ring'' magazine Fighter of The Year]] and as the [[Sugar Ray Robinson Award|Boxing Writers Association of America's Fighter of the Year]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kim |first1=Steve |title=2022 Fighter of the Year: Dmitry Bivol |url=https://www.ringtv.com/648595-2022-fighter-of-the-year-dmitry-bivol/ |website=The Ring |access-date=24 December 2023 |date=13 January 2023}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=2023-01-09 |title=The BWAA Announces Its 2022 Annual Award Winners |url=https://www.bwaa.org/single-post/the-bwaa-announces-its-2022-annual-award-winners |access-date=2024-09-20 |website=boxingwriters |language=en}}</ref> He is the only boxer to defeat two reigning [[List of undisputed world boxing champions|undisputed world champions]] in the "four-belt era".<ref>{{Cite web |title=Dmitry Bivol has now beaten two reigning undisputed world champions |url=https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=1029099362583385&id=100064499927862 |access-date=February 24, 2025 |website=Facebo

