'''Lynne Marie Stewart''' (December 14, 1946 – February 21, 2025) was an American actress,<ref name="Monush2000">{{cite book|last=Monush|first=Barry|title=John Willis Screen World 1995: With Full Color Highlights of the Film Year|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C7Qh8xVipgYC&pg=PA79|accessdate=July 3, 2012|date=February 1, 2000|publisher=Hal Leonard Corporation|isbn=9781557832337|pages=79–}}</ref><ref name="Wittebols2003">{{cite book|last=Wittebols|first=James H.|title=Watching M*A*S*H, Watching America: A Social History of the 1972-1983 Television, American Graffiti 1973, played Bobbie, Series|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CMPx-jksa6IC&pg=PA193|accessdate=July 3, 2012|date=September 1, 2003|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9780786417018|pages=193–}}</ref> widely known for her performance as Miss Yvonne,<ref name="Bellomo2012">{{cite book|last=Bellomo|first=Mark|title=Totally Tubular '80s Toys|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=owSL7Hh3HvkC&pg=PT445|accessdate=July 3, 2012|date=January 1, 2012|publisher=Krause Publications|isbn=9781440216466|pages=445–}}</ref> "the Most Beautiful Woman in Puppet Land." She originated the role in the 1981 stage show ''[[The Pee-wee Herman Show]]'', continuing it on the CBS television show ''[[Pee-wee's Playhouse]]'', the 2010 Los Angeles stage revival, and the [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]] production which opened in November 2010 at the [[Stephen Sondheim Theatre]].<ref name=castcomplete>{{cite news|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/142522-Casting-Complete-for-Broadways-Pee-wee-Herman-Show-Lynne-Marie-Stewart-Is-Miss-Yvonne|title=Casting Complete for Broadway's Pee-wee Herman Show; Lynne Marie Stewart Is Miss Yvonne|last=Jones|first=Kenneth|date=August 31, 2010|work=[[Playbill]]|accessdate=July 3, 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130404095537/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/142522-Casting-Complete-for-Broadways-Pee-wee-Herman-Show-Lynne-Marie-Stewart-Is-Miss-Yvonne|archive-date=April 4, 2013}}</ref> Stewart was also known for her recurring role on the [[FX (TV channel)|FX]]/[[FXX]] television series ''[[It's Always Sunny in Philadelphia]]'' as Charlie Kelly's mother Bonnie.<ref>{{cite news |title=Lynne Marie Stewart Dies: ‘Pee-wee’s Playhouse’ & ‘It’s Always Sunny In Philadelphia’ Actress Was 78 |url=https://deadline.com/2025/02/lynne-marie-stewart-dies-78-1236298142/ |date=February 22, 2025 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |last1=Garner |first1=Glenn |accessdate=February 22, 2025 |archive-date=February 22, 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222163334/https://deadline.com/2025/02/lynne-marie-stewart-dies-78-1236298142/ |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=castcomplete/>

