'''Stephanie Lynn Nicks''' (born May 26, 1948)<ref>{{cite book |title=Who's Who of American Women 2004–2005 |publisher=[[Marquis Who's Who]] |page=1011 |date=2004 |edition=24 |isbn=978-0837904306}}</ref> is an American singer-songwriter, known for her work with the band [[Fleetwood Mac]] and as a solo artist.

After starting her career as a duo with her then-boyfriend [[Lindsey Buckingham]], releasing the album ''[[Buckingham Nicks]]'' to little success, Nicks joined Fleetwood Mac in 1975, helping the band to become one of the [[List of best-selling music artists|best-selling music acts of all time]] with over 120 million records sold worldwide. ''[[Rumours (album)|Rumours]]'', the band's second album with Nicks, became one of the [[List of best-selling albums|best-selling albums worldwide]], being certified 20× platinum in the US.<ref name="Gold & Platinum">{{Cite web|title=Gold & Platinum|url=https://www.riaa.com/gold-platinum/|access-date=September 15, 2021|website=RIAA|language=en-US}}</ref> In 1981, while remaining a member of Fleetwood Mac, Nicks began her solo career, releasing the studio album ''[[Bella Donna (album)|Bella Donna]]'', which topped the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] and has reached [[RIAA certification|multiplatinum]] status.<ref>{{certification Cite|region=United States|type=album|artist=Stevie Nicks|title=Bella Donna}}</ref> She has released eight studio albums as a solo artist and seven with Fleetwood Mac, selling a certified total of 65 million copies in the U.S. alone.<ref name="Gold & Platinum" />

